## Background and Motivation

ValidatableTypeInfo and ValidatablePropertyInfo both have an abstract `GetValidationAttributes` today.

The implementations **always** use the same reflection code by the source-generated code today.

Instead of that, I propose making it virtual, pull up the default source-generated implementation in that implementation. If implementors wants to provide a different implementation, that still can do so by overriding the method.

## Proposed API

```diff
namespace Microsoft.Extensions.Validation;

public abstract class ValidatablePropertyInfo : IValidatablePropertyInfo
{
-      protected abstract ValidationAttribute[] GetValidationAttributes();
+      protected virtual ValidationAttribute[] GetValidationAttributes();
}

public abstract class ValidatableTypeInfo : IValidatableTypeInfo
{
-      protected abstract ValidationAttribute[] GetValidationAttributes();
+      protected virtual ValidationAttribute[] GetValidationAttributes();
}
```

## Usage Examples

Not different from today. The source-generated implementation that exists today is only lifted up one level. Other implementations can continue to override `GetValidationAttributes` as normal.

